reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars About the best you can expect on a refresh of a refresh.
reviews.reviewText: I bought 3 of these to build 3 systems at the same time. They all function fine and hit the advertised speeds, when it's not thermal throttling itself. This generation has far less overclocking headroom then previous generations of intel hedt non x299 cpus so hitting that silicon lottery really does matter. Seeing the differences between 3 shows how far this platform had been pushed by intel, as with each chip you expect there to be some variance but these have far more then any of the pervious generations I've overclocked and I've been doing this since you had to change a crystal to get an overclock. Hopefully Alder Lake will be a whole lot better, but this is still a decent cpu for the money. Be sure to use good cooling, even at stock frequencies it does need to be well cooled to keep it under the thermal throttle point and TVB/TAU limits.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fast, powerful, runs cool on 120mm air
reviews.reviewText: I specifically selected this 10th gen over 11th and 12th gens i9/i7 as I wanted the 10 regular cores. My i9-10900K runs fully unlocked on an Asus ProArt Z490-CREATOR 10G cooled by a Noctua NH-U12A chromax.black 120mm. Boosts to 5.3GHz w/o problem. Tested with Cinebench R23 10 minutes runs, it stays under 85C and then comes back to under 30C very fast. Intel Extreme Tuning Utility stress tests stay under 80C. Light load (e-mail, internet browsing, etc) runs at ~7C over room temperature. A 30 megapixels DSLR raw image gets converted in less than 5 seconds. No problem with USB and SATA storage devices (have more than 6 attached). Very happy with this CPU and zero regrets not going with a newer version.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fast delivery, brand new product as described
reviews.reviewText: Edited after exactly 1 month of use:THIS CPU IS A BEAST!!! IT RUNS EVERYTHING. With a good Cooler, Thermal Paste, and Case with good airflow it runs around 25-27° degrees doing normal stuff like navigating, and 32-38°C playing. Haven't got mayor temperatures playing games but it also depend on what are you playing. For example is not the same playing 2D than 3D or Open-World games. Have been playing shooters, GTA V and 2D platformers. One time I rendered a model on blender and it went to 60°C but it was a one time thing, also I was using the integrated graphics (UHD 630) so the CPU couldn't resist that much. With a decent GPU runs smoothly.Anyway... What are you waiting to buy this?First of all, I must clarify that I've bought directly from 'amazon.com' and not any other third party store.At first I was a little worried that the box would come with that square shape and not with the fancy one, but doing some research I realized that after the next generation intel came out, they simplified the 10th generation box so no problem with that, also it's just a box so who really cares.By the way I checked the CPU thoroughly and it doesn't have any details, it's completely new and it came with all its certification, stamps, even its manual and everything well sealed and no fingerprints anywhere.To finish, the package was intact and very well protected. I could buy again here. 10 out of 10, four spoons, A+, a regular.. tomato? 🍅 Whatever that means.. VERY NICEU CAESAR-CHAN!!.... I'm sorry, forget that.Finally, nice product. Thank you Amazon for everything!

reviews.reviewTitle: Best CPU a person could dream of.
reviews.reviewText: This CPU is by far the best investment I’ve slapped into my computer. Everything about it is insane. The gameplay, editing, performance and Clock speed is just phenomenal. Now I know it’s not a i9-12900K but if you’re looking for the next best I’d advise this. I have a Noctua air cooler on this and never once have I had any overheating issues after hours of gameplay or stress tests. 10/10 would recommend to anyone or everyone who’s considering.

reviews.reviewText: Personally I was scared to order such a CPU, however I just went for it and it came earlier than it should of, I built my pc up and downloaded the Intel drivers, after that I downloaded a few games and tested them out, immediately I noticed a difference, my fps doubled since my last pc. Personally I was impressed and glad that ordered it.

Super leistungsstarker Prozessor!!!Hatte schon einen recht Leistungstarken PC mit einem i7 4930k und habe mir jetzt den Rechner neu aufgebaut mit diesem Prozessor als Basis. Ich werde quasi weggepustet von der Leistung. Zusammen mit der Wasserkühlung (Corsair h100x) ist die Leistung im Gaming-, Musik- u. Videosektor dieses Prozessors mehr als Begeisternd (hab ihn auf 10 Kerne x 5,10 GHz, stabil bei 30-50°C). Multitasking der nächsten Generation ist angesagt.Außer dem Preis ist es einfach nur ein Traum :-) Aber am Ende muss ich sagen, das Geld hat sich mehr als gelohnt....
